		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Sun, Sep 24th 11:31 AM2000 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=6&mid=96964910514896&num=3&page=&post=1&replyto=96980947116126"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=96980947116126></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=759"><span id=>Adiemus</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>63 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.32]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Adiemus&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Let's look at the stats- it sorta all boils down to that:<br><br>An Erudite paladin starts with a STR of only 70, not as bad as a high elf (65), but still pretty bad. Humans start at 80 and dwarves at 100. If you want to wear that great-looking armor later on, you'll either have to spend a ton on STR-enhancing items or do without. Yes, you do get 20 points to allocate to your beginning stats, so you could raise the score to 90. I'd be more inclined to put a few of those points into AGI and DEX though, as you won't be hit as often and hit more often. Stats other than STR of note are WIS for mana (you are second from worse with a starting score of 83- only humans are worse off),&nbsp;&nbsp;and CHA for NPC/merchant interaction (pretty well off here- 80 isnt bad). Of course, your INT will be off the charts, which is helpful as you practice various skills both combat and non-combat. I would summarize by saying that Erudites just don't have the stats to make Pallys that are easily levelled (yes, there are exceptions, and I know that some of you will say that you've levelled your erudite pally to 60 and he's a monster- let me request that you compare the number of level 60 erudite paladins to the number of level 60 halfling druids to compare the relative ease of attaining that lofty level). Purely from a stat-perspective, a dwarf is the race of choice for a paladin.<br><br>Next point is Starting Area (Newbie Zone). Erudites begin life in Toxxula Forest- almost unanimously considered the worst newbie zone in Norrath. To begin with, its VERY dark (did I mention that Erudites are night blind?), there is a relative lack of low level MoBs for you to fight, and I am told that there are higher-level things that wander the zone that can and do kill newbies regularly and that the guards for whatever reason won't jump in to help you. Most Erudites quickly abandon Toxx for the better hunting in the Qeynos newbie zone, so that is an alternative. Humans (Freeport or Qeynos), dwarves (Butcherblock) and high elves (Greater Faydark) all get clearly superior newbie zones. In terms of hunting from level 1 to 15, I'd give the edge to dwarves or high elves, due to having places such as Crushbone nearby with MoBs of challenge and good xp/loot and quests that can be done to give you a boost.<br><br>Plusses: well, you'll certainly stand out from the crowd. Do a /who all erudite paladin on a night where there are 2000 on your server and see if you get more than 10. Erudites certainly look noble in their pally garb as well. Roleplaying them can be a blast if only from the sheer novelty of seeing one. In all my time in EQ, I have met less than 20 erudite pallys. So they do have a unique quality to them. Sadly, that is the only real plus I can think of.</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >1 Replies</td></tr></table><table width="100%"><tr><td class=mhback>&nbsp;</td><td class=mhback >Thread Subject</a></td><td class=mhback>Started by</a></td><td class=mhback>Replies</a></td><td class=mhback>Last Post</a></td><td class=mhback>Rating</a></td></tr><tr class=mlr>
